<recipe>
    <name>Mirchi Kaa Saalan</name>
    <indexCharacter>M</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>6</servings>
    <instructions>Dry roast all ingredients in spice powder. Grind into a powder in a food processor.

Heat 3 tbsp oil in a large pan on high heat; Saute peppers until lightly blistered, about 18 minutes. Remove peppers and reserve. 

Add 3 tbsp cup canola oil to pan; fry spice powder, stirring constantly, 2 minutes; add peanut flour and stir, scraping bottom. 

Deglaze with 1 cup water, scraping bottom of pan, and cook stirring constantly 2 minutes (be careful not to burn flour). Add another cup of water and stir to combine water and spice mix; cook 3 minutes or until oil begins to form on top. Add coconut and stir; cook 4 to 5 minutes. 

Add salt and tamarind paste and stir to combine, about 1 minute.

Add 1 cup coconut milk and stir to combine. Add reserved peppers. Cover and cook on medium high about 5 minutes. Serve warm with rice and bread.</instructions>
